[[File:Magnetosphere rendition.jpg|250px|thumb|A showdown of [[Earth's magnetic field]] with [[Solar winds]].]]
The '''Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program''',<ref name="Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program"/> is a scientific mission of the Space and Upper Atmosphere Research Commission of Pakistan ([[SUPARCO]]) to undertake research in [[geophysics]], particularly [[Earth's magnetic field|geomagnetism]].<ref name="Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program">{{cite web|last=SUPARCO |title=Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program |url=http://www.suparco.gov.pk/pages/space-weather-monitoring.asp |work=Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program |publisher=Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program |accessdate=30 September 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120717021910/http://suparco.gov.pk/pages/space-weather-monitoring.asp |archivedate=17 July 2012 |df= }}</ref>  The objective of the mission is to provide better understanding of the Earth's magnetic field, and of associated [[Geomagnetic storm|hazard mitigation]]. <ref name="Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program"/> The program monitors mathematical variation in the South Asian regional geomagnetic field.<ref name="Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program"/> Research is conducted in specially established geomagnetic observatories in Islamabad and Karachi.  Data collected provides the basis for continuous studies of Earth's [[magnetic field]], and is made available to various national and international institutions.<ref name="Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program"/> 

The program was established in 1983 at the [[Sonmiani (space facility)|Sonmiani space facility]].  The second geomagnetic observatory was established in 2008.<ref name="Geomagnetic Observatories and their Applications">{{cite web|title=Workshop On Geomagnetic Observatories and their Applications |url=http://www.suparco.gov.pk/pages/space-weather-course-site/index.html |publisher=Geomagnetic Observatories and their Applications |accessdate=30 September 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120717021036/http://suparco.gov.pk/pages/space-weather-course-site/index.html |archivedate=17 July 2012 |df= }}</ref>  Suparco regularly releases a public domain bulletin of geomagnetic data to national and international users, <ref name="Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program"/><ref>{{cite web|last=SUPARCO |title=Geomagnetic Field Monitoring |url=http://www.suparco.gov.pk/pages/ionospheric-geomagnetic.asp#iono5 |accessdate=30 September 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304042424/http://www.suparco.gov.pk/pages/ionospheric-geomagnetic.asp |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df= }}</ref>  containing research on the effects of [[solar flare]]s and severe magnetic storms recorded by the observatories.<ref name="Geomagnetic Field Monitoring Program"/>

