'''Skifska''' is a [[license block]] located in the [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] zone on the continental shelf of the [[Black Sea]]. It was awarded in 2012 to a consortium consisting of [[Royal Dutch Shell]], [[ExxonMobil]], [[Petrom]] and [[Nadra]].
Original plans intended to start the exploration programme in 2015 on the block with estimated [[natural gas]] and [[Natural gas condensate|condensates]] resources in the range of {{convert|200|to|250|e9m3}}.<ref name=reuters150812> {{cite news | url = https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/08/15/us-shell-exxonmobil-ukraine-idUSBRE87E0C320120815 | title = Exxon, Shell-led group win $10 billion Ukraine gas project | first = Pavel | last = Polityuk | agency = [[Reuters]] | date = 2012-08-15 | accessdate = 2014-03-28}} </ref> Potential future production contingent to success during the exploration campaign could yield around {{convert|550|e6cuft/d}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.2b1stconsulting.com/exxonmobil-and-shell-won-bid-on-black-sea-skifska-gas-field/|title=ExxonMobil and Shell won bid on Black Sea Skifska gas field|date=2012|publisher=2b1stconsulting.com|accessdate=2013-04-28}}</ref>
Royal Dutch Shell stopped their negotiations over a [[production sharing agreement]] in January 2014.<ref name=reuters190314> {{cite news | url = https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/03/19/ukraine-crisis-shell-idUSL6N0MG40H20140319 | title = Shell pulled out of gas field talks in Ukraine in January | first = Natalia | last = Zinets | agency = [[Reuters]] | date = 2014-03-19 | accessdate = 2014-03-28}} </ref> Due to the [[2014 Crimean crisis]] the project was put on hold in March 2014.<ref name=dallas>{{cite news | title=Exxon Mobil puts Ukraine gas prospect on hold|url=http://www.dallasnews.com/business/energy/20140305-exxon-mobil-puts-ukraine-gas-prospect-on-hold.ece|publisher=Dallas News|accessdate=19 March 2014}}</ref>
